"title": "4836: light, and people of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4836: light, and people of god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture often uses light as a symbol of the people of God, and especially the manner in which believers are able and required to reflect the glory of God in a dark world of sin.</p>\n<h2>The people of God as the light of the world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:14-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:14–5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:5-Ps37:6\">PSA 37:5–37:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:18\">PRO 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:9\">PRO 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:8-Isa58:10\">ISA 58:8–58:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:1-Isa60:5\">ISA 60:1–60:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:1\">ISA 62:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:3\">DAN 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:32\">LUK 2:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:47\">ACT 13:47</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of believers acting as light to the world</h2>\n<p>Moses on Mount Sinai:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:29-Exod34:30\">EXO 34:29–34:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:35\">EXO 34:35</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:3-2Sam23:4\">2SA 23:3–23:4</a> <em>the righteous ruler, fully realised in Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:21-Job29:25\">JOB 29:21–29:25</a> <em>Job as a counsellor</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:35\">JHN 5:35</a> <em>John the Baptist</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:15\">ACT 6:15</a> <em>Stephen</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:15\">PHP 2:15</a> <em>the Philippian church</em></p>\n<h2>God is the source of the light of his people</h2>\n<h3>God and his law as the source of light</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:1\">PSA 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:27\">PSA 118:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:31\">JDG 5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:13-Job11:17\">JOB 11:13–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:27-Job22:28\">JOB 22:27–22:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:8\">PSA 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:5\">PSA 34:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:13\">PSA 56:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:11\">PSA 97:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:23\">PRO 6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:1\">ECC 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:19-Isa60:20\">ISA 60:19–60:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:5\">JHN 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The gospel of forgiveness as a source of light</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:17-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:17–26:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:28-Job33:30\">JOB 33:28–33:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:4\">PSA 112:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:2\">ISA 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:18\">ISA 29:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:16\">MAT 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:19-John3:21\">JHN 3:19–3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:18\">EPH 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:27\">EPH 5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:4\">HEB 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:32\">HEB 10:32</a></p>\n<h2>The people of God are called to live in his light</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8-Eph5:14\">EPH 5:8–5:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:9\">PSA 36:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:15\">PSA 89:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:5\">ISA 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:8\">LUK 16:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4\">JHN 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:35-John12:36\">JHN 12:35–12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:12\">ROM 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:5-1Thess5:6\">1TH 5:5–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:8-1John2:10\">1JN 2:8–2:10</a></p>",
